token_info.name: Tripofobic Device for Diagnosic Test
token_info.description: A sensory stimulant for the primary purpose of improving the auditory/spatial skills of the target with respect to distraction (FDR); however, this method was considered too fragile and not well suited to achieve a functional effect in the general population. On a 6 month follow up study of 6 patients, it was found that for a given dose of Tripofobic, 1 of 6 of the 6 patients were able to perform a 2.25 m.D and 7 of the 7 were able to do a 1 m.D.
